Task: Use reload(true) for autoload instrumentation

Summary: Fixed coverage instrumentation failing on autoload scripts with active instances.
Godot creates all autoload instances before calling _ready(), so reload() returned
ERR_ALREADY_IN_USE. Changed to reload(true) (keep_state=true) which keeps instances
while recompiling source with instrumented code.

Files modified:
- src/gd_tools/addons/gd-tools-coverage/coverage.gd: reload() -> reload(true), removed ERR_ALREADY_IN_USE dead code
- tests/fixtures/gdscript/test_coverage_instrumentation.gd: Rewrote 2 tests for keep_state behavior
- tests/e2e/test_autoload_coverage_e2e.py: Updated docstring and assertion message
- tests/fixtures/autoload_coverage/scripts/game_state.gd: Updated comment
- tests/fixtures/autoload_coverage/scripts/chimera_data.gd: Updated comment

